What:		/sys/class/watchdog/watchdogn/activations
Date:		August 2017
Contact:   	Milton Miller <miltonm@us.ibm.com>
Description:
		It is a read-write file. It contains a count of times
		the watchdog device had been activated since the couter
		was reset.  Writing 0 to the device will reset the counter.
		Support for this counter and its range is hardware specific.

What:		/sys/class/watchdog/watchdogn/boot_activations
Date:		August 2017
Contact:   	Milton Miller <miltonm@us.ibm.com>
Description:
		It is a read only file. It contains a count of times
		the watchdog device had been activated at boot since the
		couter was reset.  Support for this counter and its range
		is hardware specific.

